   "source": [
    "# 34. Why does L2 regularization give sparse coefficients?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5c4304b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "That statement is actually incorrect—and interviewers love this trap.\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ First, correct the premise\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 L2 regularization does not give sparse coefficients.\n",
    "👉 L1 regularization does.\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ What L2 Regularization actually does\n",
    "\n",
    "In models like linear/logistic regression, L2 adds a penalty:\n",
    "\n",
    "Loss=Error+λ∑w^2i\n",
    "\n",
    "Penalizes large weights\n",
    "Shrinks coefficients toward zero\n",
    "But rarely makes them exactly zero\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Result: dense model (most features remain)\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ What gives sparsity? → L1 Regularization\n",
    "\n",
    "Penalizes absolute values:\n",
    "\n",
    "λ∑∣wi∣\n",
    "Can push some weights exactly to zero\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Result: sparse model (feature selection)\n",
    "\n",
    "🧠 Intuition (Very Important)\n",
    "🔹 L2 (Ridge)\n",
    "Smooth penalty (quadratic)\n",
    "Shrinks weights evenly\n",
    "Keeps all features\n",
    "🔹 L1 (Lasso)\n",
    "Sharp corners in penalty (diamond shape)\n",
    "Forces some weights to exact zero\n",
    "🎯 Geometric Insight (Interview Favorite)\n",
    "L1 constraint → diamond shape → hits axes → zeros\n",
    "L2 constraint → circle → rarely touches axes → no zeros\n",
    "🔥 Why people confuse this?\n",
    "\n",
    "Because both:\n",
    "\n",
    "Reduce overfitting\n",
    "Shrink coefficients\n",
    "\n",
    "But only L1 → feature selection\n",
    "\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Perfect)**\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “L2 regularization does not produce sparse coefficients; it shrinks them toward zero but keeps all features. Sparsity is achieved with L1 regularization because its penalty can drive some coefficients exactly to zero.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip (Use this to impress interviewer)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “L1 performs feature selection, while L2 performs weight shrinkage.”"
   ]
  },
